import tdsvis
tdsvis.offline()

tdsvis.demo()

The bottom network is a standard networkx graph with dict data structures on each node. The stacked area chart is from a pandas.DataFrame.

Key features

When you hover over the wind_gen legend on the network, it highlights the data on the network and the stacked area chart.

Similarly, if you hover over thermal_gen_1, it hightights this node on the graph too.

Hovering over either graph will show the coresponding node data in the table if it exists.

If you type "gen" in the search box, you'll highlight names that have that substring in them on both graphs.

General

This works for any networkx graph and pandas.DataFrame where the node names have a corresponding element in the dataframe
